Just another run really. A lot of costly deaths, a few brain farts. Realized very early on that I was on pace, and started to play more safely the further I got in, opting out of Lake Skip and a few other short cuts that aren't quite consistent enough on my end yet to warrant the risk.

Biggest panic moments are the last room of Oshiro (which is always painful if you die late there), a really bad run-in with a Seeker, and an earlier room in Mirror Temple where I mixed up what strat I wanted to use. The Badeline fight had a lot of little hiccups too. Summit was mostly okay; in fact I've never sub-12'd Summit before. When I got to 3000M and saw how far ahead I was, I got a little too excited and slipped up early on, but managed to pull it together (mostly) for the end.

I think Old Site was really the only chapter where everything went just how I wanted. On the bright side, plenty of room for improvement!
